President Barack Obama has proclaimed June 2015 as African-American Music Appreciation Month. In his proclamation, he recognizes the significant contributions of African-American musicians to American music and culture. He highlights how their music has helped shape the nation, capturing the essence of who we are as Americans. Obama emphasizes that African-American music has not only brought people together but also empowered them to strive for a more inclusive and equal society. He calls upon public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe the month with activities and programs that raise awareness and appreciation of music composed, arranged, or performed by African Americans.